Here's the approach:

**1. Define theme resource dictionaries** — one per theme:

```xml
<!-- Themes/LightTheme.xaml -->
<ResourceDictionary xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui"
                    xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml">
    <Color x:Key="PageBackground">#FFFFFF</Color>
    <Color x:Key="PrimaryText">#1A1A1A</Color>
    <Color x:Key="Accent">#0078D4</Color>
</ResourceDictionary>
```

Create matching `DarkTheme.xaml` and `HighContrastTheme.xaml` with different color values but the **same keys**.

**2. Create a theme service** to swap dictionaries at runtime:

```csharp
public enum AppTheme { Light, Dark, HighContrast }

public static class ThemeService
{
    public static void ApplyTheme(AppTheme theme)
    {
        var mergedDicts = Application.Current!.Resources.MergedDictionaries;

        // Remove existing theme dictionary (always the last one added)
        mergedDicts.Clear();

        var themeDictionary = theme switch
        {
            AppTheme.Dark => new DarkTheme(),
            AppTheme.HighContrast => new HighContrastTheme(),
            _ => new LightTheme()
        };

        mergedDicts.Add(themeDictionary);

        // Persist the choice
        Preferences.Set("AppTheme", theme.ToString());
    }
}
```

**3. Apply the saved theme on startup** in `App.xaml.cs`:

```csharp
public App()
{
    InitializeComponent();

    var saved = Preferences.Get("AppTheme", nameof(AppTheme.Light));
    var theme = Enum.Parse<AppTheme>(saved);
    ThemeService.ApplyTheme(theme);
}
```

**4. Use `DynamicResource`** (not `StaticResource`) in your XAML so changes propagate immediately:

```xml
<ContentPage BackgroundColor="{DynamicResource PageBackground}">
    <Label TextColor="{DynamicResource PrimaryText}" Text="Hello" />
</ContentPage>
```

**5. Settings page picker:**

```xml
<Picker x:Name="ThemePicker" Title="Theme"
        ItemsSource="{Binding Themes}"
        SelectedIndexChanged="OnThemeChanged" />
```

```csharp
void OnThemeChanged(object sender, EventArgs e)
{
    var selected = (AppTheme)ThemePicker.SelectedIndex;
    ThemeService.ApplyTheme(selected);
}
```

**Key points:**
- `DynamicResource` is essential — it re-evaluates when the dictionary changes.
- Keep resource keys identical across all theme dictionaries.
- Use `Preferences` to persist the user's choice across launches.
